Other contestants are Sebastian Nzau, Jonathan Maweu, and Francis Musembi who are vying as independent candidates. 

All the 1, 335 polling stations across the county opened their doors by 6 am. At Mlolongo Primary School which has 44 polling stations, voters trooped in one by one as officials decried low turn-out. 






The by-election comes when the country is battling a spike in Covid-19 infections. Voters are required to wear masks and wash their hands as they enter the polling stations. Maendeleo Chap Chap leaders maintains that the party made a wise decision. Mr Muthama’s estranged wife facing public scrutiny over questionable academic credentials. Ex-Epra boss Pavel Oimeke resigned last week from to venture into politics. Andayi says it was unfortunate that the NLC official died under mysterious circumstances.